title.value: Изготовление вакцины живой против реовирусного теносиновита птиц с использованием СПФ-эмбрионов кур и ее иммунологические свойства
Manufacturing of a live vaccine against avian reovirus tenosynovitis with use of SPF-chicken embryos and it immunological properties
Manufacturing of a live vaccine against avian reovirus tenosynovitis with use of SPF-chicken embryos and it immunological properties

journal.title: Agriculture - Problems and Prospects : collection of scientific papers

person.name: Radyush, I.S., National Academy of Sciences. Scientific and Practical Center of Animal Breding (Belarus). The S.N. Vyshelesskij Inst. of Experimental Veterinary Medicine

abstract.value: In the conditions of the Republic of Belarus there were presented the results of studies of the way of avian reovirus tenosynovitis life vaccine production with the help of SPF-chicken embryos. In experiences SPF-embryos of hens by 9-daily incubation and strain 'S1133' of birds' reovirus were used. The results prove that chickens being vaccinated with the experimental series of the above mentioned vaccine in the age of 7 and 35 days on the 21st day after the first vaccination have antibodies in titer 1728,6+-141,8 on the 7th, 14th, 21st, and 30th day after the second vaccination antibodies titer in blood definitely increases relative to antibodies titer on the 21st day after the first vaccination and gets to 2433+-239, 2095,6+-253,7, 2587+-293,9 and 2574,8+-263,0 accordingly. This fact proves of high-level immunity maturation and high immunogenic activity of vaccine, received from birds' reovirus tenosynovitis strain 'S1133' by cultivation on SPF- embryos.
